%N A080019 Positive integers such that the smallest positive real solution to x^n + x = 2*Pi*a(n) forms a monotonically increasing sequence as n grows.
%C A080019 Solutions satisfy cos(x^n)=cos(x), the limit of the smallest real root also being the limit of a(n+1)/a(n) -> 2.2397...
%e A080019 Smallest real roots r(n) of equation x^n + x = a(n)*2*Pi, for n=2...8, are: x^2 + x = 1*(2*Pi), r(2)=2.0560009...; x^3 + x = 2*(2*Pi), r(3)=2.1817119...; x^4 + x = 4*(2*Pi), r(4)=2.1886076...; x^5 + x = 9*(2*Pi), r(5)=2.2233125...; x^6 + x = 20*(2*Pi), r(6)=2.2313694...; x^7 + x = 45*(2*Pi), r(7)=2.2372063...; x^8 + x = 101*(2*Pi), r(8)=2.2393436...
